@page "/refresher"
<PageTitle>Refresher Course for Licensed Drivers</PageTitle>

<Transition>
<div class="course-page refresher">

  <section class="intro">
    <h1>Refresher Course – Get Back Behind the Wheel with Confidence</h1>
    <p>
      The <b>Refresher Course</b> is designed for licensed <b>AZ, DZ, or G</b> drivers who want to rebuild confidence,
      update their skills, or return to the trucking industry after a break.
    </p>
    <p>
      Our professional instructors will assess your current driving ability and customize a training plan to match your
      specific needs — from yard work to on-road performance and modern compliance standards.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="overview">
    <h2>Program Overview</h2>
    <p>
      The refresher training helps experienced drivers return safely and confidently to commercial driving.  
      Each session is one-on-one with a certified instructor using late-model commercial trucks.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Flexible duration — 1 to 5 days depending on skill level</li>
      <li>Practical training in yard and on-road conditions</li>
      <li>Focus on inspection, gear shifting, and backing techniques</li>
      <li>Safety and defensive driving review</li>
      <li>Updated Hours-of-Service and logbook (ELD) training</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="training">
    <h2>Training Modules</h2>
    <div class="facts">
      <div><b>Pre-Trip Inspection:</b> refresh your knowledge of vehicle safety checks and defect detection.</div>
      <div><b>Coupling &amp; Uncoupling:</b> proper fifth-wheel and air line connection procedures.</div>
      <div><b>Backing &amp; Parking:</b> practice straight-line, offset, and alley dock maneuvers.</div>
      <div><b>On-Road Driving:</b> real-traffic training — city, rural, and highway operation.</div>
      <div><b>Safety &amp; Compliance:</b> defensive driving, logbook updates, and cargo securement rules.</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="requirements">
    <h2>Who Should Take This Course?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Drivers returning to work after a long break</li>
      <li>Foreign-licensed drivers seeking Ontario experience</li>
      <li>Fleet drivers preparing for re-evaluation or upgrade</li>
      <li>Owner-operators who want a safety performance review</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="pricing">
    <h2>Program Options &amp; Tuition</h2>

    <div class="tier">
      <h3>Standard Refresher — <span>$850</span></h3>
      <ul>
        <li>8 hours of one-on-one instruction</li>
        <li>Pre-trip + on-road assessment</li>
        <li>Use of training truck</li>
        <li>Certificate of completion</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="note">Perfect for experienced drivers returning after a short absence.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="tier premium">
      <h3>Professional Re-Entry Package — <span>$1,500</span></h3>
      <ul>
        <li>20 hours total training (yard + road)</li>
        <li>Advanced defensive and mountain driving</li>
        <li>Full safety and compliance review</li>
        <li>Job placement assistance with partner carriers</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="note">Best for drivers returning to long-haul or cross-border operations.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="career">
    <h2>Why Take a Refresher?</h2>
    <p>
      Commercial driving standards evolve — staying current keeps you safe, compliant, and employable.
      Our instructors work with real carriers, ensuring you meet today’s performance expectations.
    </p>

    <div class="compare">
      <table>
        <tr>
          <td><span>Recommended For:</span> <b>AZ / DZ / G Drivers</b></td>
          <td><span>Duration:</span> 1–5 days (custom schedule)</td>
          <td><span>Focus Areas:</span> Inspection, driving, safety, compliance</td>
          <td><span>Result:</span> Confidence, certification, and job readiness</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="faq">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Do I need to have a valid license?</h3>
      <p>Yes. A valid AZ, DZ, or G license is required before starting this course.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Is this course suitable for foreign-licensed drivers?</h3>
      <p>Yes. We provide Ontario-standardized training for foreign drivers seeking local experience.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Can companies send their drivers for re-training?</h3>
      <p>Absolutely. We provide corporate refresher programs customized for fleets.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Will I get a certificate?</h3>
      <p>Yes. Upon completion, you’ll receive a Refresher Course Certificate recognized by carriers and safety departments.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

</div>
</Transition>
